# Enforce LF line endings in the working tree on every platform.
#
# install.sh and its helpers run under bash on both macOS and Windows
# (Git Bash). Mixed line endings cause two real problems:
#
# 1. Shell scripts with CRLF fail on macOS/Linux at the shebang line
#    (#!/usr/bin/env bash\r is not a valid interpreter). Git Bash on
#    Windows tolerates this, so the bug stays latent until the script
#    runs on a Mac.
#
# 2. diff_skill in install.sh streams files through sed for placeholder
#    substitution. On Git Bash, sed normalizes CRLF -> LF on output,
#    which would silently corrupt the diff against an installed file
#    that retained CRLF — making every update see false "content
#    differs" drift for any placeholder-bearing skill.
#
# `text=auto eol=lf` makes git store and check out every text file with
# LF on both platforms. Binary files are auto-detected and left alone.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-braces for files that absolutely must be LF.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.mjs text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
